	p can have interactiosn between variables
	p Linear models can represent complex non-linear relationships.
	p If the underlying relationship is non-linear, for example \(E(Y|X)=5+3x^2\), we can still represent this as a linear model.
	p We can create a new variable \(z=x^2\) and then use the model:
	p \(y=\theta_+\theta_1z\)


